cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper deals with the identification of the architecture and weights of a neural network, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of ReLU activation functions and the analysis of their piecewise linear nature suggest that computer vision (cs.CV) may also be a relevant sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the implications of their findings for neuroscience (cs.NE) and security (cs.SY), indicating that these sub-categories may also be relevant. Finally, the use of algorithms to identify the units and weights in the network suggests that artificial intelligence (cs.AI) may also be a relevant sub-category.
